#originalTopic=Debate:_Homosexuals_in_the_US_military
"Don't ask don't tell" traumatizes many gay troops. Jeff Cleghorn, a former lawyer with the Servicemembers Legal Defense Network, a gay-rights group monitoring military justice, said to the Washington Post in June 18, 2004 article, "In the case of some, they get in the Army and they are traumatized by an awareness that the military is 20 years behind the societal curve."[13] 
